He released his debut album, “Billy Ocean,” in 1976, and he has gone on to release 10 more, including “Suddenly” (1984) and “Love Zone” (1986), which were both certified 2x Platinum in the U.S. and Gold in the U.K. Ocean is known for hit songs such as “Love Really Hurts Without You,” “When the Going Gets Tough, the Tough Get Going,” “Get Outta My Dreams, Get into My Car,” and the Grammy-winning “Caribbean Queen (No More Love on the Run).

New Update: 15-Year-Old Ridge Girl Who Went Missing Twice In Week Found
item.description: A Long Island teenager who was reported missing twice in a week has been found. Shyma Dahoui, age 15, left a relative’s home in Shoreham, located on Vee Jay Drive, at around 1:30 a.m. Tuesday, May 30, according to Suffolk County Police. On Sunday, June 4, police announced that Dahoui had been located and was unharmed. Original story: Police are asking for help in locating a Long Island teenager who has gone missing for the second time in a week.
